HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 290
By Bulso
A RESOLUTION to recognize Curt Masters on the occasion of his
retirement.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that the members of this General Assembly should honor
those citizens who have performed with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm throughout their
careers; and
WHEREAS, Curt Masters is one such estimable person, who has served with distinction
for more than twenty-five years as headmaster of Brentwood Academy and will be taking a
much-deserved retirement at the end of the 2024-2025 school year; and
WHEREAS, throughout his exemplary career as an education administrator, Mr. Masters
has distinguished himself as a public-spirited citizen of the highest order and as an exceptional
asset to his community and this State; and
WHEREAS, Brentwood Academy is a co-educational, independent, college preparatory
school, dedicated to nurturing and challenging each whole person—body, mind, and spirit—to
the glory of God; and
WHEREAS, under Curt Masters's leadership, Brentwood Academy has flourished,
achieving academic excellence and fostering a supportive and nurturing environment for its
students; and
WHEREAS, his steadfast commitment to educational excellence has been evident
through his emphasis on academics, athletics, arts, and character education; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Masters's visionary leadership has helped Brentwood Academy achieve
outstanding academic success and produce some of the best and brightest students in our
State and nation; and
WHEREAS, his retirement marks the culmination of a remarkable career devoted to
educational excellence and the betterment of young lives; and
